olic value.</p><ul><li>In UX, <code>assert_</code> returns <code>false</code> if and only if <code>not value</code> is <b>satisfiable</b>.</li><li>In OX, <code>assert_</code> returns <code>true</code> if and only if <code>not value</code> is <b>unsatisfiable</b>.</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-nondet_UNSAFE\"><a href=\"#val-nondet_UNSAFE\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> nondet_UNSAFE : <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-ty\">Value.ty</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-t\">Value.t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Do not use <code>nondet_UNSAFE</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-nondet\"><a href=\"#val-nondet\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> nondet : <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-ty\">Value.ty</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-t\">Value.t</a></span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>nondet ty</code> creates a fresh variable of type <code>ty</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-simplify\"><a href=\"#val-simplify\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> simplify : <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-t\">Value.t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-t\">Value.t</a></span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>simplify v</code> simplifies the value <code>v</code> according to the current path condition.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-fresh_var\"><a href=\"#val-fresh_var\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> fresh_var : <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-ty\">Value.ty</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><a href=\"../Var/index.html#type-t\">Var.t</a> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-branch_on\"><a href=\"#val-branch_on\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> branch_on : \u000A  <span><span class=\"optlabel\">?left_branch_name</span>:string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"optlabel\">?right_branch_name</span>:string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span><a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-sbool\">Value.sbool</a> <a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-t\">Value.t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">then_</span>:<span>(<span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">else_</span>:<span>(<span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-if_sure\"><a href=\"#val-if_sure\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> if_sure : \u000A  <span><span class=\"optlabel\">?left_branch_name</span>:string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"optlabel\">?right_branch_name</span>:string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span><a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-sbool\">Value.sbool</a> <a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-t\">Value.t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">then_</span>:<span>(<span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">else_</span>:<span>(<span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>if_sure cond ~then_ ~else_</code> evaluates the <code>~then_</code> branch if <code>cond</code> is guaranteed to hold in the current context, and otherwise evaluates <code>~else_</code>.</p><p>This is to be used with caution: the <code>~then_</code> branch should <em>always</em> describe a behaviour that is semantically equivalent to that of the <code>~else_</code> branch when <code>cond</code> holds.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-branch_on_take_one\"><a href=\"#val-branch_on_take_one\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> branch_on_take_one : \u000A  <span><span class=\"optlabel\">?left_branch_name</span>:string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"optlabel\">?right_branch_name</span>:string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span><a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-sbool\">Value.sbool</a> <a href=\"argument-1-Sol/Value/index.html#type-t\">Value.t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">then_</span>:<span>(<span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">else_</span>:<span>(<span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Branches on value, and (<b>in UX only</b>) takes at most one branch, starting with the <code>then</code> branch. This means that if the <code>then_</code> branch is SAT, it is taken and the <code>else_</code> branch is ignored, otherwise the <code>else_</code> branch is taken. In OX mode, this behaves exactly as <code>branch_on</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-give_up\"><a href=\"#val-give_up\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> give_up : <span>string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Gives up on this path of execution for incompleteness reason. For instance, if a give feature is unsupported.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-with_frame\"><a href=\"#val-with_frame\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> with_frame : <span>string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span>)</span> <span class=\"a